  "text": "Although the studies from which these data were drawn differed in some particulars, all had a common core of methods, including double-blind placebo crossover designs, consistent doses of caffeine (3.3 mg/kg, average 260 mg/person), [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] 14 All subjects were men in otherwise good health on the basis of physical examination and medical history. Among diagnosed hypertensives, 11 men were taking ACE inhibitors (nϭ7), ␤-blockers (nϭ2), or hydrochlorothiazide (nϭ2). All hypertensive medications were tapered accordingly before the BP screening. Seven men from the clinic were recently diagnosed but not yet medicated.",
